    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "honestly that sounds kind of one sided. u basically just said one side is about inclusion and the other side is just \"resistance.\" a lot of the parents i know aren't trying to be \"resistant,\" they're just worried about whether these topics are age-appropriate or if they should have a say in when their kids learn this stuff. isnt there a valid argument for parental rights in education too?",
